grade: Jōyō kanji, taught in junior high
on reading compounds: 架空【カクウ】aerial, overhead, fictitious, imaginary, fanciful, fabricated
kun reading compounds: 架ける【かける】to suspend between two points, to build (a bridge, etc.), to put up on something (e.g. legs up on table)
架かる【かかる】to span, to bridge, to cross, to straddle
